internet was growing at' b" a rate of twenty percent a *month.* the number of `host'" b' machines with direct connection to tcp/ip has been doubling' b' every year since the internet is moving out of its' b' original base in military and research institutions, into' b' elementary and high schools, as well as into public libraries' b' and the commercial sector.' b'' b'references' b'==========' b'' b'bowers, k., t. laquey, j. reynolds, k. roubicek, m. stahl, and a.' b'yuan, ``where to start a bibliography of general internetworking' b"information'' (rfc-1175), cnri, u texas, isi, bbn, sri, mitre," b'august b'' b"the whole internet catalog user's guide by ed krol. b"o'reilly and associates, inc." b'---' b'a clear, non-jargonized introduction to the intimidating business' b'of network literacy written in humorous style.' b'' b"krol, e., ``the hitchhikers guide to the internet'' (rfc-1118)," b'university of illinois urbana, september b'' b"``the user's directory to computer networks'', by tracy laquey." b'' b'the matrix: computer networks and conferencing systems worldwide.' b'by john quarterman. digital press: bedford, ma. b'---' b'massive and highly technical compendium detailing the' b'mind-boggling scope and complexity of global internetworks.' b'' b'donnalyn frey and rick adams.' b'' b'the internet companion, by tracy laquey with jeanne c. ryer b'addison wesley.' b'---' b"``evangelical'' etiquette guide to the internet featuring" b'anecdotal tales of life-changing internet experiences. foreword' b'by senator al gore.' b'' b"zen and the art of the internet: a beginner's guide by brendan p." b'kehoe prentice hall.' b'---' b'brief but useful internet guide with plenty of good advice on' b'useful databases.' b'' b'' b'see also ftp.eff.com:/pub/internet-info/. (thanks to bruce sterling' b'' b'' b'general' b'=======' b'' b'cunningham, scott and alan l. porter. ``communication networks: a' b"dozen ways they'll change our lives.'' the futurist b'(january-february, b'' b'bri